<item>
            <title>[HIVE-23408] Hive on Tez :  Kafka storage handler broken in secure environment</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HIVE-23408</link>
                <project id="12310843" key="HIVE">Hive</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;hive.server2.authentication.kerberos.principal set in the form of hive/_HOST@REALM,&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Tez task can start at the random NM host and unfold the value of _HOST with the value of fqdn where it is running. this leads to an authentication issue.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;for LLAP there is fallback for LLAP daemon keytab/principal, Kafka 1.1 onwards support delegation token and we should take advantage of it for hive on tez.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
